3. cs.SI (Signal Processing) - The paper involves linear precoding and interference cancellation techniques, which are fundamental signal processing techniques. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses physical-layer multicasting, which is relevant to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper involves mathematical analysis and optimization of communication systems, which can be considered as a computational engineering problem.
